-- Wanda Commercial Properties sets up $1.6 bln JV to invest in Australia
-- By Clare Jim
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 10:38PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 12 (Reuters) - Wanda Commercial Properties <0169.HK> said on Tuesday that it will set up a joint venture valued at HK$12.5 billion ($1.6 billion) with its parent to invest in Australian real estate as part of a strategy to diversify its earnings.

The joint venture will initially invest around HK$2.1 billion in a mixed-use commercial project in Queensland, Wanda Commercial Properties said.  Wanda Commercial Properties will hold a 60 percent stake in the joint venture, said the Hong Kong-listed arm of China's largest commercial developer Dalian Wanda Commercial Properties.